# Accessibility and motion

Canonical behavior: `@src/scripts/main.js`, `@src/styles/global.css` (`.reveal`), `@src/components/Nav.astro`, `@src/components/Contact.astro`.

## Controls

- Icon-only links/buttons need `aria-label`.
- Disclosure menus: `aria-expanded` on the toggle; `aria-hidden` on the panel when closed.
- Decorative SVGs/images: `aria-hidden="true"` (and empty `alt` on `<img>`).

## Motion

- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` for parallax, continuous animation, and non-essential transforms.
- Scroll listeners: `{ passive: true }`; batch visual updates with `requestAnimationFrame`.
- Entrance motion: `.reveal` + IntersectionObserver; add `.is-visible` once, then `unobserve`.

```js
// ❌ BAD: scroll handler that writes layout every event, ignores reduced motion
// ✅ GOOD: matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)'), rAF throttle, unobserve after reveal
```

## Forms

- Success/error messages: `role="status"` and `aria-live="polite"` (see contact form success in Contact).
